Operation Flashpoint: Cold War Crisis (Czech: Operace Flashpoint) is a 2001 tactical shooter simulation video game developed by
 Bohemia Interactive Studio and published by Codemasters. Set during the Cold War in 1985, the game follows United States Armed 
Forces personnel in various combined arms roles as they combat a rogue Soviet
 Armed Forces field army invading the fictional island countries of Everon and Malden. 